    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Hungarian Chamber to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 3 September
                    1549)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">The King has to negotiate with the Dóczy–Lipcsey family.
                            They say they still have the letter in which Queen Beatrix transferred
                            the castles of Slovenská Ľupča and Šášov to Orbán Dóczy for 8,000
                            florins. According to the János Zomor, it is not a big problem to
                            recover the Šášov castle for the royal treasury. They thought that
                            Christoph Konritz, the prefect of the Banská Bystrica copper mines, knew
                            the case well, and when they wrote to him, Konritz answered that indeed
                            that letter is in Oláh’s hands, and he last saw it a year ago. So they
                            ask him to send the original letter to the Chamber so they can start the
                            administration. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad dominum cancellarium.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Reverendissime Domine, nobis Observandissime, servitiorum <choice>
                        <orig>nostrae</orig>
                        <supplied>nostrorum</supplied>
                    </choice> commendationem!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Cogitur <persName>maiestas regia</persName>, dominus noster
                    clementissimus quotannis numerare dominis nobilibus <persName>Doczy</persName>
                    et <persName>Lyppchey</persName> iuxtam factam cum eis transactionem <del
                        corresp="author">numerare</del> certam summam pecuniae. Et non obscure
                    dicitur exstare adhuc litteras quondam <persName>Beatricis reginae</persName>,
                    quibus inscripsisset tam <del corresp="author">eam</del> arcem Lypche,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Castle of Zólyomlipcse, Ľupčiansky hrad
                        today.</note> quam Saskew<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Castle of
                        Saskő, Šášovský hrad today.</note> quondam reverendissimo domino
                        <persName>Urbano episcopo thesaurario</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">Orbán Dóczy of Nagylucse (†1491) was Bishop of Eger.</note>
                    pro octo millibus Florenorum.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.4"> Beatrice of
                        Aragon, Queen of Hungary gave these two castles to the Dóczy family via <hi
                            rend="italic">inscriptio</hi>, which was why the family was in constant
                        litigation regarding these possessions, see <hi rend="smallcap">Wenzel</hi>
                        1876, 19–20.</note> Contulimus de his cum domino <persName>directore
                        causarum regiarum</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">János
                        Zomor.</note> qui asserit posse non magno negotio <del corresp="author"
                        >tibi</del> recuperari arcem Saskew pro fisco regio, liberarique <choice>
                        <orig>maiestate</orig>
                        <supplied>maiestas</supplied>
                    </choice> regia ab praedicta pensione et obligatione. Existimabamus autem domino
                        <persName>Christofero Kewrish</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6"
                        >Christoph Konritz. On the contract regarding the handover of the two
                        castles in return for an annual amount of 600 florins, see ÖStA FHKA
                        Hoffinanz–Ungarn RN 2. Konv. 1549 fol. 147–150.</note> praefecto fodinarum
                    cupri Novosoliensis rem exactuus constare, ad quem cum scripsissemus, respondit
                    haberi eas ipsas litteras apud manus Dominationis Vestrae Reverendissimae, quas
                        <del corresp="author">ut</del> scribit se anno proxime praeterito vidisse
                    immo et processum, quem pro recuperatione castrorum illorum instituisset felicis
                    memoriae quondam dominus <persName>Ludovicus rex</persName>.<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.7">King Louis II. In fact, King Wladislaus II confirmed
                        Beatrice of Aragon’s donation, see <hi rend="smallcap">Ortvay</hi> 1894,
                        65.</note> Quare Dominatio Vestra Reverendissima de voluntate sacrae regiae
                    maiestatis (ad quam etiam per annexas scripsimus) velit praedictas litteras
                    originales in specie ad hanc regiam cameram dirigere, ut communicatore,
                    directore et aliis fidelibus servitoribus suae maiestatis consilio incipiamus
                    rem aggredi, in commodum et voluntatem domini nostri clementissimi.
                    Reverendissimam Dominationem Vestram Deus servet feliciter.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Posonii</placeName> die 3. Septembris anno 1549.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Reverendissimae Dominationis Vestrae deditissimi servitores.</p>
            </div>
